##Questions\
\
Q1: To what degree do traits vary within/between sites?\
Q2: To what degree is trait variance associated with different taxonomic levels?\
\
Based on previous studies (discussed above), our specific hypotheses are that:\
\
H1: the majority of trait variation will probably be between sites (because abiotic variables ,e.g. temperature and precipitation, are more highly variable between sites, thus acting as a stronger selective pressure), indicating that species turnover is the process shaping the local plant community\
\
H2: the majority of trait variation will probably be within species-level (because the plants on Gongga are specifically adapted to a small range of environmental variation), indicating that competitive displacement is the process shaping the local plant community \
